3
00:00:33,583 --> 00:00:35,750
Tell me!

4
00:00:41,083 --> 00:00:42,208
[NARRATOR]
Upon Tohka's arrival

5
00:00:42,291 --> 00:00:44,208
in this strange new world,

6
00:00:44,291 --> 00:00:46,833
she was immediately
faced with a challenge.

7
00:00:46,916 --> 00:00:48,000
She could choose
to fight against

8
00:00:48,083 --> 00:00:50,541
the appetite of her
growing curiosity,

9
00:00:50,625 --> 00:00:52,708
or feed it generously with love.

10
00:00:52,791 --> 00:00:56,833
And today, Shido's wallet is
also feeling conflicted.

11
00:02:20,291 --> 00:02:22,708
[FEMALE CLERK]
Thank you! Please come again!

12
00:02:24,166 --> 00:02:26,083
[SHIDO]
Here you go.

13
00:02:26,166 --> 00:02:28,083
Ooohhh...

14
00:02:29,750 --> 00:02:31,666
Is this a test?
Am I about to fail?

15
00:02:31,750 --> 00:02:34,416
Uh, no. It's for you.
Stop drooling.

16
00:02:37,833 --> 00:02:40,625
Wow!

17
00:02:40,708 --> 00:02:41,625
[TOHKA chewing]

18
00:02:41,708 --> 00:02:42,791
Is this one of
those date things?

19
00:02:42,875 --> 00:02:45,250
[SHIDO]
No, it's bread.

20
00:02:45,333 --> 00:02:46,416
Okay.

21
00:02:46,500 --> 00:02:48,125
Is that another name for "date"?

22
00:02:48,208 --> 00:02:49,833
I don't understand how
something so delicious

23
00:02:49,916 --> 00:02:51,083
can't be called a date.

24
00:02:51,166 --> 00:02:53,250
You can call it
one if you want to.

25
00:02:53,333 --> 00:02:55,583
Fascinating. Even though
this was delicious,

26
00:02:55,666 --> 00:02:57,875
it's still not good enough
to be called a date.

27
00:02:57,958 --> 00:03:00,750
And so the mystery continues.

28
00:03:01,916 --> 00:03:03,166
There's one!

29
00:03:03,250 --> 00:03:04,541
[SHIDO] Not quite!

30
00:03:04,625 --> 00:03:07,666
All these persons.
Where'd they come from?

31
00:03:07,750 --> 00:03:09,458
Is this war?

32
00:03:09,541 --> 00:03:10,916
If that's the case,

33
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:12,833
I better attack before the
Mecha-Mecha Squad gets here.

34
00:03:12,916 --> 00:03:14,500
No, wait! You don't
want to do that!

35
00:03:14,583 --> 00:03:16,375
[TOHKA] Why are you stopping
me from saving us?

36
00:03:16,458 --> 00:03:18,500
[SHIDO] I'm not!
There's nothing to save us from.

37
00:03:18,583 --> 00:03:20,500
No one is trying to hurt us!

38
00:03:22,541 --> 00:03:25,166
[BOY]
Look, Mama.

39
00:03:25,250 --> 00:03:27,708
See? I threw it in
the trash all by myself!

40
00:03:27,791 --> 00:03:30,333
[MOTHER] Wow!
What a good boy you are!

41
00:03:41,375 --> 00:03:43,041
[TOHKA giggles]

42
00:03:43,125 --> 00:03:46,333
[TOHKA] What about right now?
This moment? Is this a date?

43
00:03:46,416 --> 00:03:48,791
[SHIDO] Not really.
But you're getting closer.

44
00:03:48,875 --> 00:03:52,208
[TOHKA] Dates are
complicated matters.

45
00:03:52,291 --> 00:03:54,791
Ah! Look! That thing
over there looks yummy!

46
00:03:54,875 --> 00:03:57,416
How in the world are
you still hungry?

47
00:03:57,500 --> 00:03:59,916
Am I cray or is that
Shido with a new girl?

48
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:02,416
Omigosh does that mean
he's cheating on Tonomachi?

49
00:04:02,500 --> 00:04:03,958
