50
00:04:05,041 --> 00:04:08,250
[ORIGAMI] That woman.
I know she's a Spirit.

51
00:04:08,333 --> 00:04:10,500
But there's no spatial quake.

52
00:04:10,583 --> 00:04:12,583
Sergeant Origami reporting.

53
00:04:12,666 --> 00:04:17,000
A-0613. Need an observation
device immediately.

54
00:04:19,750 --> 00:04:21,458
Outrageous!

55
00:04:21,541 --> 00:04:24,625
I can't believe humans each
such amazingly delicious things!

56
00:04:24,708 --> 00:04:26,666
Heh, heh. Oh hey, Tohka.

57
00:04:26,750 --> 00:04:29,708
What happened after
you left yesterday?

58
00:04:29,791 --> 00:04:31,375
Same thing as usual.

59
00:04:31,458 --> 00:04:34,875
I swing my sword around some.
I blast the artillery.

60
00:04:34,958 --> 00:04:38,041
In the end, my body disappeared
naturally like it always does.

61
00:04:38,125 --> 00:04:39,416
[SHIDO]
Disappeared?

62
00:04:39,500 --> 00:04:41,666
[TOHKA] Yes, I go to a world
different from this one.

63
00:04:41,750 --> 00:04:43,250
It's a dark space.

64
00:04:43,333 --> 00:04:45,541
Once I get there,
I just fall asleep.

65
00:04:45,625 --> 00:04:48,083
So you mean, when you
wake up, you come here?

66
00:04:48,166 --> 00:04:50,250
[TOHKA] Well, I don't
wake up on my own.

67
00:04:50,333 --> 00:04:52,125
It's more like by force.

68
00:04:52,208 --> 00:04:54,500
And it has nothing to
do with what I want.

69
00:04:54,583 --> 00:04:57,000
I'm just pulled here.
Usually, anyway.

70
00:04:57,083 --> 00:04:58,625
[SHIDO] By force?

71
00:04:58,708 --> 00:05:02,000
Then Spirits don't cause
spatial quakes on purpose.

72
00:05:02,083 --> 00:05:05,291
They must just be accidents.

73
00:05:05,375 --> 00:05:08,416
By "usually" you mean
today was different?

74
00:05:08,500 --> 00:05:09,916
How would I know?

75
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:11,000
Please tell me.

76
00:05:11,083 --> 00:05:12,625
Look, that might
actually be the reason

77
00:05:12,708 --> 00:05:14,208
there wasn't a
spatial quake today.

78
00:05:14,291 --> 00:05:15,750
You're too persistent.

79
00:05:15,833 --> 00:05:18,083
Besides, I have important things
to do, like find more food!

80
00:05:18,166 --> 00:05:20,416
Tohka, come on. Wait!

81
00:05:20,500 --> 00:05:22,083
I should've brought more money.

82
00:05:22,916 --> 00:05:26,333
[RYOKO] It looks like
she's a 98.5 percent match.

83
00:05:26,416 --> 00:05:29,625
That's way too high to be
a coincidence, of course.

84
00:05:29,708 --> 00:05:31,416
But why is she here?

85
00:05:31,500 --> 00:05:33,625
She isn't wearing her
Spirit armor right now.

86
00:05:33,708 --> 00:05:35,666
If we want to attack,
this is it.

87
00:05:35,750 --> 00:05:37,166
[RYOKO]
Think about where you are.

88
00:05:37,250 --> 00:05:39,791
You know we can't
afford to be reckless.

89
00:05:41,750 --> 00:05:44,041
[TOHKA] What kind
of place is this?

90
00:05:44,125 --> 00:05:46,208
[SHIDO]
Uh, an expensive one.

91
00:05:46,291 --> 00:05:47,500
I don't know what that means.

92
00:05:47,583 --> 00:05:48,333
I'm going in.

93
00:05:48,416 --> 00:05:49,458
No! Wait, hold on!

94
00:05:49,541 --> 00:05:52,083
[TONOMACHI]
Well, if it isn't Shido!

95
00:05:52,166 --> 00:05:53,000
[SHIDO]
Tonomachi?

96
00:05:53,083 --> 00:05:55,125
[TONOMACHI]
Hmm...

97
00:05:55,208 --> 00:05:56,583
