first time you've failed

248
00:11:30,458 --> 00:11:32,541
with that tactic, is it Kawagoe?

249
00:11:32,625 --> 00:11:34,791
[SHIIZAKI] Fact established,
and acknowledged.

250
00:11:34,875 --> 00:11:36,291
Classic Shido.

251
00:11:36,375 --> 00:11:39,208
He always insists on doing
everything in a proper order.

252
00:11:39,291 --> 00:11:41,291
What's that? Rain?

253
00:11:41,375 --> 00:11:42,541
[REINE] Strange.

254
00:11:42,625 --> 00:11:45,500
There weren't any rain
clouds in the vicinity.

255
00:11:45,583 --> 00:11:48,583
[KOTORI] Oh, well.
Maybe it's for the best.

256
00:11:50,791 --> 00:11:51,583
[gasps]

257
00:11:51,666 --> 00:11:53,458
Where did you bring me?

258
00:11:53,541 --> 00:11:56,041
Is this the secret base
of the Mecha-Mecha Squad?

259
00:11:56,125 --> 00:11:58,208
[SHIDO]
Of course not. Don't worry.

260
00:12:06,333 --> 00:12:08,583
[TOHKA] Why can't I get you,
you unruly chicken!

261
00:12:08,666 --> 00:12:10,666
Shido! Tell this
thing to cooperate!

262
00:12:10,750 --> 00:12:12,208
I told you. This
is a really tough one.

263
00:12:12,291 --> 00:12:13,958
You have to
have a strategy,

264
00:12:14,041 --> 00:12:16,000
and yelling through
the glass doesn't work.

265
00:12:16,083 --> 00:12:18,250
Fine! Then how?

266
00:12:18,333 --> 00:12:19,458
[SHIDO]
This one should be easy.

267
00:12:19,541 --> 00:12:20,875
It's sticking up.

268
00:12:21,958 --> 00:12:24,500
That's not the one I want.
I want the chicken.

269
00:12:24,583 --> 00:12:27,916
Okay. Well, maybe there's
another one like it somewhere.

270
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:29,666
Ha, ha, ha, ha, ha!

271
00:12:29,750 --> 00:12:31,708
I can get you whichever
prize you want!

272
00:12:31,791 --> 00:12:34,125
Come on! Pick one!

273
00:12:36,041 --> 00:12:37,791
[SHIDO]
Maybe that one.

274
00:12:37,875 --> 00:12:39,125
I've got it!

275
00:12:39,208 --> 00:12:42,333
Listen closely. I'll
use this button over here.

276
00:12:42,416 --> 00:12:44,708
You use the one on
your side there.

277
00:12:44,791 --> 00:12:47,000
Let go when I give the signal.

278
00:12:47,083 --> 00:12:48,541
It's worth a shot.

279
00:12:55,750 --> 00:12:59,666
[SHIDO]
Wait for it. Wait for it.

280
00:12:59,750 --> 00:13:01,333
Wait for it.

281
00:13:02,625 --> 00:13:03,541
Now!

282
00:13:03,625 --> 00:13:05,333
Let it go, Tohka!

283
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:11,958
Chicken!

284
00:13:12,041 --> 00:13:14,291
Hold on! It still
hasn't dropped yet!

285
00:13:22,250 --> 00:13:24,500
[SHIDO] I'm so sorry;
that was totally my fault.

286
00:13:24,583 --> 00:13:26,708
I didn't give good instructions.

287
00:13:26,791 --> 00:13:28,916
Drop the chicken!

288
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:31,458
Please drop it! Why
won't you listen to me?

289
00:13:31,541 --> 00:13:33,500
Shido and I worked
so hard on this.

290
00:13:33,583 --> 00:13:35,750
Drop it! Please!

291
00:13:35,833 --> 00:13:36,833
It's okay.

292
00:13:36,916 --> 00:13:39,083
I'm begging you!
Drop it, you have to!

293
00:13:39,166 --> 00:13:41,666
Please!

294
00:13:51,791 --> 00:13:53,333
[chuckles]

295
00:13:53,416 --> 00:13:55,250
[BOTH]
We did it!

296
00:13:57,083 --> 00:14:00,333
[TOHKA] Question. What method
do those use to transform?

297
00:14:00,416 --> 00:14:02,708
[SHIDO] Actually,
trains don't transform.

298
00:14:02,791 --> 00:14:04,791
[TOHKA] What?
So they use fusion?

299
00:14:04,875 --> 00:14:06,875
[SHIDO] Well, they do
connect to each other.

300
00:14:06,958 --> 00:14:09,500
[TOHKA]
Oh, wow!

301
00:14:09,583 --> 00:14:12,500
Thank you. I had
so much fun today.

302
00:14:12,583 --> 00:14:14,583
[SHIDO] Good. Me too.
Thanks for coming.

303
00:14:14,666 --> 00:14:16,083
[TOHKA] I am a
little disappointed

304
00:14:16,166 --> 00:14:18,375
that we didn't get to
explore Dream Park.

305
00:14:18,458 --> 00:14:21,250
[SHIDO] Oh, it's
totally overrated!

306
00:14:21,333 --> 00:14:24,583
[TOHKA]
If you say so. But Shido?

307
00:14:24,666 --> 00:14:27,750
The day is almost over and
I still didn't see a date.

308
00:14:27,833 --> 00:14:29,750
Can you tell me
what one is like?

309
00:14:29,833 --> 00:14:31,500
[SHIDO] A date is just
when a girl and a boy

310
00:14:31,583 --> 00:14:33,625
go out and have a
good time together.

311
00:14:33,708 --> 00:14:35,375
You can't actually see one.

312
00:14:35,458 --> 00:14:36,958
[TOHKA]
Oh, that makes sense!

313
00:14:37,041 --> 00:14:40,375
Well in that case, I would say
we had a wonderful date today!

314
00:14:40,458 --> 00:14:42,791
[SHIDO]
Uh, sure.

315
00:14:43,958 --> 00:14:46,541
[TOHKA]
I like dates. They're nice.

316
00:14:47,583 --> 00:14:50,208
Not good. I can't
believe I'm seeing this.

317
00:14:50,291 --> 00:14:52,333
A Spirit shows up
without a spatial quake

318
00:14:52,416 --> 00:14:55,458
and then connects
with a human boy.

319
00:14:55,541 --> 00:14:56,875
Permission to shoot, Miss?

320
00:14:56,958 --> 00:14:59,416
[RYOKO] Not yet. Still
waiting to hear from the top.

321
00:14:59,500 --> 00:15:01,916
This is a very
unusual situation.

322
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:06,208
No one's been evacuated.
We'll just have to wait and see.

323
00:15:06,291 --> 00:15:07,958
Point Alpha here.

324
00:15:08,041 --> 00:15:09,708
What happened?

325
00:15:09,791 --> 00:15:11,375
What?

326
00:15:11,458 --> 00:15:14,166
We've got permission to shoot?

327
00:15:14,250 --> 00:15:16,833
[TOHKA] All the humans
were very kind today.

328
00:15:16,916 --> 00:15:18,916
[SHIDO] No one tried
to kill you, did they?

329
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:20,833
I knew you'd be okay.

330
00:15:20,916 --> 00:15:23,208
[TOHKA]
Yeah. You're right.

331
00:15:23,291 --> 00:15:25,583
I never knew the
world was so kind,

332
00:15:25,666 --> 00:15:29,000
so much fun, and so beautiful.

333
00:15:29,083 --> 00:15:30,958
I love it here.

334
00:15:31,041 --> 00:15:35,500
And now, I understand why the
Mecha-Mecha Squad is after me.

335
00:15:35,583 --> 00:15:37,458
Because whenever I
appear in this world,

336
00:15:37,541 --> 00:15:38,916
something bad happens.

337
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:42,000
I ruin something beautiful.
I ruin your world.

338
00:15:42,083 --> 00:15:43,750
[SHIDO]
That's not true.

339
00:15:43,833 --> 00:15:45,666
So listen, I've been thinking

340
00:15:45,750 --> 00:15:50,250
and it's better if I
don't exist anymore.

341
00:15:50,333 --> 00:15:52,500
[SHIDO]
Don't say that!

342
00:15:52,583 --> 00:15:53,708
We're fine!

343
00:15:53,791 --> 00:15:55,500
There was no spatial
quake today, was there?

344
00:15:55,583 --> 00:15:57,458
You didn't ruin anything!

345
00:15:57,541 --> 00:15:59,375
[TOHKA]
Yes, but that doesn't mean

346
00:15:59,458 --> 00:16:02,000
there won't be one
the next time I appear.

347
00:16:02,083 --> 00:16:03,958
Once I go back and fall asleep,

348
00:16:04,041 --> 00:16:06,000
I won't be able
to control myself.

349
00:16:06,083 --> 00:16:08,125
[SHIDO] Fine! Then I guess
you just can't go back!

350
00:16:08,208 --> 00:16:10,208
--Huh?
--Have you ever even tried?

351
00:16:10,291 --> 00:16:12,458
Just once. Just
try staying here!

352
00:16:12,541 --> 00:16:14,875
[TOHKA] Even if I did,
there are so many things

353
00:16:14,958 --> 00:16:16,291
I don't know about this world.

354
00:16:16,375 --> 00:16:18,041
[SHIDO] I'll teach you
whatever you don't know!

355
00:16:18,125 --> 00:16:20,791
[TOHKA] Then I'd need food
and a place to sleep.

356
00:16:20,875 --> 00:16:22,916
What if something happens
we're not prepared for?

357
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:24,583
[SHIDO] I'm going
to take care of you!

358
00:16:24,666 --> 00:16:26,541
If something comes up
that we need to deal with,

359
00:16:26,625 --> 00:16:28,000
we'll deal with it.

360
00:16:28,083 --> 00:16:29,333
[TOHKA]
Are you sure?

361
00:16:29,416 --> 00:16:31,583
Am I even allowed to be here?

362
00:16:31,666 --> 00:16:33,875
Is it okay for me to be
alive in this world?

363
00:16:33,958 --> 00:16:36,041
[SHIDO]
Yes! It is!

364
00:16:36,125 --> 00:16:38,666
[TOHKA] You're the only one
who would say that to me.

365
00:16:38,750 --> 00:16:40,958
Humans like the
Mecha-Mecha Squad,

366
00:16:41,041 --> 00:16:42,625
they don't want to risk it.

367
00:16:42,708 --> 00:16:45,166
They don't want something
as dangerous as me nearby.

368
00:16:45,250 --> 00:16:46,666
[SHIDO]
I don't care about them!

369
00:16:46,750 --> 00:16:48,916
Even if everyone
else rejects you,

370
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:51,166
it doesn't change the
fact that I accept you

371
00:16:51,250 --> 00:16:54,875
and I don't want you to leave!

372
00:16:54,958 --> 00:16:56,291
Take my hand.

373
00:16:56,375 --> 00:16:59,208
That's the only job
you have right now.

374
00:17:04,625 --> 00:17:06,708
[RYOKO] Distance:
Five hundred twelve, fifteen.

375
00:17:06,791 --> 00:17:08,583
Wind direction:
Forty-point-eight.

376
00:17:08,666 --> 00:17:10,541
Wind speed: zero-point-four.

377
00:17:10,625 --> 00:17:12,458
Temperature:
twenty-four degrees,

378
00:17:12,541 --> 00:17:15,833
RH: fifty-two point eight.
We're all clear.

379
00:17:15,916 --> 00:17:16,458
[gunshot]

380
00:17:16,541 --> 00:17:17,291
[SHIDO] Tohka!

381
00:17:17,375 --> 00:17:19,041
[TOHKA yells]

382
00:17:19,125 --> 00:17:20,708
What are you doing?

383
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:30,625
[thud]

384
00:17:36,458 --> 00:17:39,208
[RYOKO]
Origami? Origami, come in!

385
00:17:39,291 --> 00:17:41,041
Origami?

386
00:17:47,250 --> 00:17:49,250
Shido.

387
00:17:59,500 --> 00:18:02,833
I thought maybe if you were
here for me it would be okay.

388
00:18:02,916 --> 00:18:07,333
Might be hard, but I'd be able
to do it with you by my side.

389
00:18:07,416 --> 00:18:10,833
I can get through anything
when I'm with you.

390
00:18:10,916 --> 00:18:13,208
But it doesn't matter.

391
00:18:13,291 --> 00:18:16,500
It's no use!
You're gone now!

392
00:18:16,583 --> 00:18:18,125
I'm on my own.

393
00:18:18,208 --> 00:18:20,750
This world has rejected me!

394
00:18:31,125 --> 00:18:33,541
Adonai Merek!

395
00:18:53,958 --> 00:18:55,458
Sandalphon!

396
00:19:12,875 --> 00:19:14,541
Halvanhelv!

397
00:19:14,625 --> 00:19:17,041
How dare you!

398
00:19:17,125 --> 00:19:19,291
How dare you reject me!

399
00:19:25,500 --> 00:19:26,833
[RYOKO] No way.

400
00:19:26,916 --> 00:19:29,000
Origami, retreat immediately!

401
00:19:29,083 --> 00:19:30,958
Support troops, where are you?

402
00:19:31,041 --> 00:19:33,500
Origami? Do you read me?

403
00:19:37,500 --> 00:19:39,166
So it was you.

404
00:19:39,250 --> 00:19:42,791
You're the one who did it.
You killed my only friend.

405
00:19:42,875 --> 00:19:46,541
And with him, my soul.
Just admit it.

406
00:19:46,625 --> 00:19:49,333
[ORIGAMI] Yes.
I killed Shido Itsuka.

407
00:19:49,416 --> 00:19:50,708
[TOHKA] Kill her.

408
00:19:50,791 --> 00:19:54,041
She must pay for
what she's done.

409
00:19:54,125 --> 00:19:56,083
She must die.

410
00:19:57,500 --> 00:19:59,083
[SHIIZAKI] It doesn't look
like a pulse or heart rate

411
00:19:59,166 --> 00:20:00,500
is registering for Shido.

412
00:20:00,583 --> 00:20:01,708
[NAKATSUGAWA] The spatial
quake alarm is going off.

413
00:20:01,791 --> 00:20:03,208
This can't be good.

414
00:20:03,291 --> 00:20:04,625
[MIKIMOTO] Resident evacuation
is still at seven percent.

415
00:20:04,708 --> 00:20:06,958
[KOTORI] We're lucky there
aren't many houses nearby,

416
00:20:07,041 --> 00:20:08,458
but at this rate, the whole town

417
00:20:08,541 --> 00:20:11,500
will be decimated
within minutes.

418
00:20:11,583 --> 00:20:14,166
If she were a knight, she would
have earned a passing grade,

419
00:20:14,250 --> 00:20:16,416
but if she gets herself
killed as a princess,

420
00:20:16,500 --> 00:20:19,500
then she's obviously not
worth our concern. Hm?

421
00:20:19,583 --> 00:20:21,625
[KAWAGOE] Excuse me, Commander.
What have we heard about Shido?

422
00:20:21,708 --> 00:20:23,708
[KOTORI] Oh, I wouldn't
worry too much about him.

423
00:20:23,791 --> 00:20:26,125
My brother won't be finished
off by something like that.

424
00:20:26,208 --> 00:20:27,333
[GROUP] Huh?

425
00:20:29,250 --> 00:20:30,875
There it is.

426
00:20:38,541 --> 00:20:42,125
[SHIDO] Hot! Hot, hot, hot,
hot, hot, hot, hot, hot, hot!

427
00:20:42,208 --> 00:20:43,333
Huh?

428
00:20:43,416 --> 00:20:44,750
Where am I?

429
00:20:44,833 --> 00:20:46,708
[MINOWA] Commander,
what-- What do we do now?

430
00:20:46,791 --> 00:20:48,166
[KOTORI]
I already told you.

431
00:20:48,250 --> 00:20:50,958
Even if Shido dies, he'll be
able to start a new game.

432
00:20:51,041 --> 00:20:52,875
So what the heck are
you dragging ass for?

433
00:20:52,958 --> 00:20:54,708
Get down there and
recover him immediately.

434
00:20:54,791 --> 00:20:56,625
No one else is able to stop her.

435
00:20:56,708 --> 00:20:58,291
It has to be him.

436
00:20:58,375 --> 00:21:01,916
That's right. With the method
we decided to save for last.

437
00:21:09,291 --> 00:21:10,791
[ORIGAMI] I did it.

438
00:21:10,875 --> 00:21:12,791
I killed someone.

439
00:21:12,875 --> 00:21:16,041
[TOHKA screams]

440
00:21:16,125 --> 00:21:19,250
[ORIGAMI]
I'm like them. The Spirits.

441
00:21:19,333 --> 00:21:20,666
We're the same.

442
00:21:23,291 --> 00:21:26,000
[TOHKA screams]

443
00:21:27,583 --> 00:21:29,458
[ORIGAMI yells]

444
00:21:37,166 --> 00:21:38,666
We must end this.

445
00:21:38,750 --> 00:21:41,375
[ORIGAMI]
Dad? Mom?

446
00:21:41,458 --> 00:21:42,583
I'm sorry.

447
00:21:42,666 --> 00:21:45,666
Shido. I promise to avenge you.

448
00:21:45,750 --> 00:21:49,833
[SHIDO screams]

449
00:21:49,916 --> 00:21:51,833
What? He's alive!

450
00:21:56,750 --> 00:21:59,375
Shido? Is it really you?

451
00:21:59,458 --> 00:22:02,708
Yeah. Yeah, I think it is!

452
00:22:02,791 --> 00:22:03,791
Thank you!

453
00:22:03,875 --> 00:22:05,833
Thank you for coming back!

454
00:22:05,916 --> 00:22:08,208
Don't cry.
Everything's okay now.

455
00:22:10,291 --> 00:22:12,333
Tohka! What the heck is that?

456
00:22:12,416 --> 00:22:14,708
[TOHKA] I accidentally
unsheathed Halvanhelv.

457
00:22:14,791 --> 00:22:16,458
I have to find
somewhere to release it!

458
00:22:16,541 --> 00:22:18,666
[SHIDO] No! Hold on!
You definitely can't do that!

459
00:22:18,750 --> 00:22:20,250
[TOHKA]
Then what should I do?

460
00:22:20,333 --> 00:22:23,000
It's already reached
its critical state!

461
00:22:23,083 --> 00:22:24,500
[KOTORI]
Shido, can you hear me?

462
00:22:24,583 --> 00:22:27,333
Now is the time to use that
method I taught you earlier.

463
00:22:27,416 --> 00:22:30,000
It's the only way you'll
be able to save her.

464
00:22:31,583 --> 00:22:33,250
All right, Tohka, listen to me.

465
00:22:33,333 --> 00:22:35,458
--We have to kiss now, okay?
--We what?

466
00:22:35,541 --> 00:22:38,000
Uh, never mind.
Forget it, I'm sorry.

467
00:22:38,083 --> 00:22:39,083
There has to be another way.

468
00:22:39,166 --> 00:22:41,041
No, I just don't
know what a kiss is.

469
00:22:41,125 --> 00:22:42,833
--Huh?
--Teach me and I'll do it!

470
00:22:42,916 --> 00:22:46,458
Um, 'kay. It's where we put
our lips together and then we--

471
00:23:06,833 --> 00:23:08,208
I'm so sorry!

472
00:23:08,291 --> 00:23:10,583
They told me this was the
only way I could reverse it!

473
00:23:10,666 --> 00:23:12,458
Just don't let me go.

474
00:23:12,541 --> 00:23:15,625
I'm not ready for you
to see me naked yet.

475
00:23:19,250 --> 00:23:20,375
Shido?

476
00:23:20,458 --> 00:23:21,958
[SHIDO] Uh huh?

477
00:23:22,041 --> 00:23:25,458
[TOHKA] Will you um-- take me
out on another date sometime?

478
00:23:27,791 --> 00:23:30,916
Of course.
Any time you want to.

479
00:25:06,625 --> 00:25:10,791
Kids? I'd like to introduce
you to our new transfer student!

480
00:25:12,666 --> 00:25:14,416
[TOHKA]
I'm Tohka Yatogami.

481
00:25:14,500 --> 00:25:16,958
I'm so excited to
meet all of you!

